flowRoot.flowPara: - Each sequence of the query genome is aligned to both strands of the target genome.
...... Are plus and minus strand blocks allowed to overlap ?
- The result is a graph linking intervals in the query sequences (thus always "plus" strand) to intervals in the "plus" or "minus" strands of target sequences.
- The graph is reduced so that each interval on the query genome is paired with a single interval on the target genome, and conversely.
- For each interval on a sequence, it is possible to find which one (if any) comes next, in the 5′ to 3′ direction.
The distance between two intervals is not considered when collapsing. (Thechnically it is, but the threshold is currently set to infinity.)
